Definition: Given a string of English characters, remove all the vowels (lower case and upper case) from it and return the result string. Note that ‘y’ and ‘Y’ are not considered vowels.

Positive Examples.explanation: The vowels a, i, u are removed.
The characters yand Y are not considered as vowels as instructed.
The entire string is made of vowels. So as all of them are removed, empty string is returned.

Negative Examples.explanation: All the vowels are not removed from the given string
The character y is wrongly removed.
